Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how our Tic-Tac-Toe game collects, uses, and protects your information when you use our mobile application on Android devices.
Information We Collect
Our Tic-Tac-Toe game collects minimal information:
- Device information: Basic details about your Android device to ensure game compatibility
- Game statistics: Your game scores and progress
- Optional account information: If you choose to create an account
How We Use Your Information
We use collected information to:
- Improve game performance and user experience
- Save your game progress
- Fix bugs and technical issues
- Provide game updates
Data Storage and Security
- Your game data is stored locally on your device
- If you create an account, basic information is stored on our secure servers
- We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data
Third-Party Services
- Our game may use Google Play Services for achievements and leaderboards
- Analytics tools may be used to improve game performance
Your Rights
You can:
- Access your personal data
- Request deletion of your account and associated data
- Disable data collection through your device settings
Children's Privacy
Our game does not knowingly collect information from children under 13.
Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Please review it periodically.
Last Updated: 11/04/2025
